    "markdown": "---\nformat:\n  html:\n    css: styles.css\n    embed-resources: TRUE\n    code-fold: true\n    page-layout: full\n    fig_caption: yes\n---\n\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n\n:::\n\n::: {.cell}\n\n:::\n\n\n::: narrow-section\n\n::: {.cell}\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n```{=html}\n<div id=\"grid-container\" style=\"display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); justify-items: center;\">\n<div id=\"highlight-text\">6,338</div>\n<div id=\"highlight-text\">1,391</div>\n<div style=\"display: block; &#10;              color: #ff6400; &#10;              font-size: 1.25em; &#10;              font-family: Graphik; &#10;              font-weight: bold; &#10;              text-align: center;\">High<br>Indeterminacy</div>\n<div id=\"bold-text\">Currently Eligible for<br>Parole but in Prison</div>\n<div id=\"bold-text\">Eligible for Parole in<br>the next 1-5 years</div>\n<div id=\"bold-text\">\n<span class=\"tippy html-widget html-fill-item-overflow-hidden html-fill-item\" height=\"338px\" id=\"htmlwidget-23aae47ee894508bb3db\" width=\"100%\"></span>\n<script type=\"application/json\" data-for=\"htmlwidget-23aae47ee894508bb3db\">{\"x\":{\"opts\":{\"placement\":\"bottom\",\"flip\":true,\"theme\":\"light\",\"content\":\"To compare the degrees of indeterminacy, or unpredictability\\n   of time served, of prison-sentencing systems of different jurisdictions,\\n   we use a qualitative ranking framework based on the Robina Institute's\\n   Prison-release Discretion And Prison Population Size Report.<br><br><b>High Indeterminacy<\\/b>: >60-80 percent indeterminacy (first prospect of release at 20-39.99 percent of judicial maximum).\"},\"text\":\"<span aria-label=\\\"To compare the degrees of indeterminacy, or unpredictability\\n   of time served, of prison-sentencing systems of different jurisdictions,\\n   we use a qualitative ranking framework based on the Robina Institute's\\n   Prison-release Discretion And Prison Population Size Report.<br><br><b>High Indeterminacy<\\/b>: >60-80 percent indeterminacy (first prospect of release at 20-39.99 percent of judicial maximum).\\\" tabindex=\\\"0\\\" role=\\\"button\\\">Prison Sentencing<br>System&#9432;<\\/span>\"},\"evals\":[],\"jsHooks\":[]}</script>\n</div>\n</div>\n```\n:::\n:::\n\n:::\n\n<br>\n\n\n\n::: panel-tabset \n\n## Parole Eligibility\n\n<center>\n\n::: {.cell}\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n```{=html}\n<div id=\"body-section\">\n<br/>\n<div id=\"big-section-title\">How is Parole Release Eligibility Determined?</div>\n<br/>\n<div id=\"regular-text\">Each felony in Oklahoma  has a statutory punishment; there are currently no “classes” or “levels” of crimes as found in other states.  Inmates convicted of crimes committed on or after July 1, 1998 are eligible for parole release after serving one-third of their sentence, unless they are serving a life sentence without the possibility of parole. Inmates serving consecutive sentences are not eligible for parole consideration until one-third of the consecutive sentence has been served. However, Oklahoma has enacted truth in sentencing laws which require inmates convicted of certain crimes to serve at least 85% of their sentence of imprisonment without any reduction due to sentencing credits. Some crimes, such as first-degree rape, have statutory minimum penalties. There are also statutory minimum penalties for second or subsequent convictions for certain crimes.</div>\n<br/>\n<br/>\n<div id=\"big-section-title\">People who are Eligible for Parole</div>\n<br/>\n<div id=\"bar-chart\">\n<div id=\"htmlwidget-f71b8fa0459485484138\" style=\"width:100%;height:454px;\" class=\"highchart html-widget \"></div>\n<script type=\"application/json\" data-for=\"htmlwidget-f71b8fa0459485484138\">{\"x\":{\"hc_opts\":{\"chart\":{\"reflow\":true,\"width\":500,\"height\":350},\"title\":{\"text\":\"People who are Parole Eligible but Still in Prison by Race in 2020\"},\"yAxis\":{\"title\":{\"text\":null},\"labels\":{\"enabled\":false}},\"credits\":{\"enabled\":false},\"exporting\":{\"enabled\":true},\"boost\":{\"enabled\":false},\"plotOptions\":{\"series\":{\"label\":{\"enabled\":false},\"turboThreshold\":0,\"animation\":false,\"cursor\":\"pointer\",\"borderWidth\":3,\"minPointLength\":4},\"treemap\":{\"layoutAlgorithm\":\"squarified\"},\"accessibility\":{\"enabled\":true,\"keyboardNavigation\":{\"enabled\":true},\"linkedDescription\":\"TBD\",\"landmarkVerbosity\":\"one\"},\"area\":{\"accessibility\":{\"description\":\"TBD\"}}},\"series\":[{\"group\":\"group\",\"data\":[{\"state\":\"Oklahoma\",\"race\":\"White, non-Hispanic\",\"n\":1162,\"prop\":0.456581532416503,\"yearendpop_ped\":2545,\"prop_label\":\"46%\",\"tooltip\":\"<b>Oklahoma - White, non-Hispanic<\\/b><br>46%<br>\",\"y\":45.6581532416503,\"color\":\"#FDE725\",\"name\":\"White, non-Hispanic\",\"colorv\":\"White, non-Hispanic\"},{\"state\":\"Oklahoma\",\"race\":\"Black, non-Hispanic\",\"n\":734,\"prop\":0.2884086444007858,\"yearendpop_ped\":2545,\"prop_label\":\"29%\",\"tooltip\":\"<b>Oklahoma - Black, non-Hispanic<\\/b><br>29%<br>\",\"y\":28.84086444007858,\"color\":\"#440154\",\"name\":\"Black, non-Hispanic\",\"colorv\":\"Black, non-Hispanic\"},{\"state\":\"Oklahoma\",\"race\":\"Hispanic, any race\",\"n\":453,\"prop\":0.1779960707269155,\"yearendpop_ped\":2545,\"prop_label\":\"18%\",\"tooltip\":\"<b>Oklahoma - Hispanic, any race<\\/b><br>18%<br>\",\"y\":17.79960707269155,\"color\":\"#2C6079\",\"name\":\"Hispanic, any race\",\"colorv\":\"Hispanic, any race\"},{\"state\":\"Oklahoma\",\"race\":\"Other race(s), non-Hispanic\",\"n\":196,\"prop\":0.07701375245579568,\"yearendpop_ped\":2545,\"prop_label\":\"8%\",\"tooltip\":\"<b>Oklahoma - Other race(s), non-Hispanic<\\/b><br>8%<br>\",\"y\":7.701375245579569,\"color\":\"#6AAD69\",\"name\":\"Other race(s), non-Hispanic\",\"colorv\":\"Other race(s), non-Hispanic\"}],\"type\":\"column\",\"dataLabels\":{\"enabled\":true,\"format\":\"{point.prop_label}\",\"style\":{\"fontSize\":\"14px\",\"fontWeight\":\"bold\",\"fontFami